SETUP GUIDE

Complete Setup Instructions for YOLOv8, YOLOv11, and Faster R-CNN

This document explains how to install dependencies, prepare the dataset, and run all three object detection models included in this project.

1. System Requirements
Recommended
Python 3.10+
CUDA-enabled GPU (optional but recommended)
8GB+ RAM
Required
Git
Conda or virtual environment
2. Create Virtual Environment
conda create -n detection python=3.10 -y
conda activate detection
3. Install Core Dependencies
pip install torch torchvision torchaudio --index-url https://download.pytorch.org/whl/cu118
pip install ultralytics
pip install opencv-python
pip install numpy
pip install matplotlib
4. Dataset Setup

Your dataset should follow this structure:

data/
│── train/
│   ├── images/
│   ├── train.json
│
│── valid/
│   ├── images/
│   ├── valid.json
│
│── test/
│   ├── images/
│   ├── test.json
data.yaml (for YOLOv8 & YOLOv11)

Create a file named data.yaml:

train: data/train/images
val: data/valid/images
test: data/test/images

names:
  0: class1
  1: class2
  2: class3
5. YOLOv8 Setup
Train YOLOv8
yolo detect train model=yolov8n.pt data=data.yaml epochs=50 imgsz=640
Inference (Predictions)
yolo detect predict model=best.pt source=your_image.jpg
6. YOLOv11 Setup
Train YOLOv11
yolo detect train model=yolov11n.pt data=data.yaml epochs=50 imgsz=640
Inference
yolo detect predict model=best.pt source=your_image.jpg
7. Faster R-CNN Setup
Install TorchVision (if missing)
pip install torchvision
Train Faster R-CNN
python fasterRCNN/train.py
Inference with Faster R-CNN
python fasterRCNN/infer.py --img path/to/image.jpg
8. Large File Handling (Git LFS)

If your model file (.pth / .pt) is above 100MB, enable Git LFS:

git lfs install
git lfs track "*.pth"
git add .gitattributes
git add path/to/model.pth
git commit -m "Track large file with LFS"
git push origin main
9. Final Folder Structure
Deep-Learning-Mini-Project/
│── yolov8/
│   ├── train.py
│   ├── infer.py
│   ├── best.pt
│
│── yolov11/
│   ├── train.py
│   ├── infer.py
│   ├── best.pt
│
│── fasterRCNN/
│   ├── train.py
│   ├── infer.py
│   ├── model.pth
│
│── data/
│── SETUP.md
│── README.md
10. Troubleshooting
Not detecting classes

Check:

names: list in data.yaml
Annotation format
Training epochs
Git LFS errors

Run:

git rm --cached <large_file>

Then re-add using LFS.

11. Conclusion

This setup document provides a complete guide to installing, training, and running YOLOv8, YOLOv11, and Faster R-CNN on your system.
Use this as the standard installation reference for your project.
